When add_args is called with (13, 29):
    x0 = 13    (first argument)
    x1 = 29    (second argument)

The function should return x0+x1 = 42.

The buggy instruction:
    add x0, x0, x0     // x0 = 13 + 13 = 26  ✗

Fix: add x0, x0, x1   // x0 = 13 + 29 = 42  ✓

Remember: in AAPCS64, the first arg is in x0, the second in x1.
The return value must be placed in x0 before ret.
